@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1>Hello, world!</h1>

<p>Welcome to your new IgniteUI app.</p>

<p>
    This sample is built on the open-source, Infragistics&copy; IgniteUI MIT-licensed Blazor packages
    <a href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/IgniteUI.Blazor.Lite" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>IgniteUI.Blazor.Lite</strong></a>
    (Navbar, Nav Drawer, Button, Icon, Card, Input, Circular Progress and much more) and
    <a href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/IgniteUI.Blazor.GridLite" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>IgniteUI.Blazor.GridLite</strong></a>
    &mdash; a lightweight, sortable and filterable data grid.
</p>

<p>
    Four built-in themes &mdash; <strong>Bootstrap</strong>, <strong>Material</strong>,
    <strong>Fluent</strong> and <strong>Indigo</strong> &mdash; ship in light and dark variants.
    Swap between them by changing the stylesheet <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> in <code>App.razor</code>.
</p>

<h2>Components used in this app:</h2>

<ul>
    <li><code>IgbNavbar</code>, <code>IgbNavDrawer</code>, <code>IgbNavDrawerHeaderItem</code>, <code>IgbNavDrawerItem</code> &mdash; the side-rail navigation in the layout, with active-route highlighting via the <code>Active</code> parameter.</li>
    <li><code>IgbButton</code> &mdash; powers the increment action on the Counter page.</li>
    <li><code>IgbGridLite</code> + <code>IgbGridLiteColumn</code> &mdash; drives the table on the Weather page; supports column sort, filter and resize out of the box.</li>
    <li><code>IgbCircularProgress</code> &mdash; the loading indicator shown while the forecast is generated.</li>
</ul>

